{"type":"compaction","id":"6e9e1cb0","parentId":"28349f56","timestamp":"2026-02-21T16:15:05.550Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Modify the `Login.jsx` component to improve its structure and design using Tailwind CSS.\n- Implement a color palette including sky blue while aiming for a spontaneous look with other complementary colors.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Only perform one step at a time and wait for confirmation before proceeding.\n- Avoid excessive use of blue in the color scheme.\n- The user wants guidance in creating a color palette that works with the sky blue.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Identified the location of `Login.jsx`.\n- [x] Installed `tailwindcss`, `postcss`, and `autoprefixer` as development dependencies using `npm`.\n- [x] Removed the `styles` directory and the `globals.css` file.\n- [x] Read the contents of the `Login.jsx` file.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Modifying the `Login.jsx` component with Tailwind CSS classes and a new color palette.\n\n### Blocked\n- None\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use Tailwind CSS for styling**: Tailwind CSS was chosen to restyle the components.\n- **Remove existing CSS**: The existing CSS, including `globals.css`, was removed to allow for a fresh start with Tailwind CSS.\n- **Address `Login.jsx`**: The user wants to improve the `Login.jsx` component.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Present a modified version of `Login.jsx` with Tailwind CSS classes and a color palette applied.\n\n## Critical Context\n- File path to the `Login.jsx` component: `~/Documents/helpdesk/src/templates/src/pages/Login.jsx`\n- The desired color palette should include sky blue (`#E0FFFF`) and complementary colors like light grays (`#F9FAFB` and `#6B7280`), white (`#FFFFFF`), and potentially a touch of light yellow (`#FDE68A`) or light red (`#FCA5A5`) for accent.\n- The existing code for `Login.jsx`\n```javascript\nimport React, { useState } from 'react';\nimport { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport { login, saveAuth } from '../api/auth';\n\nexport default function Login() {\n  const [email, setEmail] = useState('');\n  const [password, setPassword] = useState('');\n  const [error, setError] = useState('');\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n\n  async function onSubmit(e) {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    setError('');\n\n    if (!email || !password) {\n      setError('Debes completar todos los campos.');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      setLoading(true);\n\n      const data = await login(email, password);\n\n      // 🔥 Guardar sesión en localStorage\n      saveAuth(data);\n\n      navigate('/');\n    } catch (err) {\n      setError(err.message || 'Credenciales incorrectas');\n    } finally {\n      setLoading(false);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <section className=\"login-page\">\n      <div className=\"login-overlay\" />\n\n      <div className=\"login-shell\">\n        <aside className=\"login-brand-panel card\">\n          <h1>Helpdesk GLPI</h1>\n          <p>Gestión moderna de soporte, inventario y usuarios.</p>\n          <ul>\n            <li>✔ Seguimiento de SLA</li>\n            <li>✔ Inventario de equipos</li>\n            <li>✔ Seguridad con Supabase Auth</li>\n          </ul>\n        </aside>\n\n        <form className=\"card login-card\" onSubmit={onSubmit}>\n          <h2>Iniciar sesión</h2>\n          <p className=\"text-muted\">Accede con tu cuenta</p>\n\n          <label>Email</label>\n          <input\n            type=\"email\"\n            value={email}\n            onChange={(e) => setEmail(e.target.value)}\n            placeholder=\"tu-correo@empresa.com\"\n            autoFocus\n            required\n          />\n\n          <label>Contraseña</label>\n          <input\n            type=\"password\"\n            value={password}\n            onChange={(e) => setPassword(e.target.value)}\n            placeholder=\"••••••••\"\n            required\n          />\n\n          <button type=\"submit\" disabled={loading}>\n            {loading ? 'Ingresando...' : 'Ingresar'}\n          </button>\n\n          {error && <p className=\"alert error\">{error}</p>}\n        </form>\n      </div>\n    </section>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user asked the assistant to push the changes they made manually in the login page to the repository.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The assistant identified the need to use `git add`, `git commit`, and `git push` commands to push the changes.\n- The assistant tried to execute all git commands at once using `&&` but failed because the shell doesn't support that.\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The previous attempt to execute all the git commands failed because the `&&` operator is not supported by the current shell.\n- Based on the previous directory assumption, the assistant assumed the repo was in `~/Documents/helpdesk`.\n- The current `workdir` value is `C:\\Users\\INVESTIGACION 185\\.openclaw\\workspace`, which is not the correct directory for the git repository.\n\n\n<read-files>\n~/Desktop/helpdesk-glpi/pom.xml\n~/Desktop/helpdesk-glpi/src/main/resources/application.properties\n~/Documents/helpdesk/src/templates/src/pages/Home.jsx\n~/Documents/helpdesk/src/templates/src/pages/Login.jsx\n</read-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"aea846a8","tokensBefore":101654,"details":{"readFiles":["~/Desktop/helpdesk-glpi/pom.xml","~/Desktop/helpdesk-glpi/src/main/resources/application.properties","~/Documents/helpdesk/src/templates/src/pages/Home.jsx","~/Documents/helpdesk/src/templates/src/pages/Login.jsx"],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":false}
